text: Nice and very reasonably priced food. Cashier named is Aishah, she can speak Mandarin because she went to a Chinese school. The food is a bit salty as they have figured out a how to make it cheap but delicious at the same, once you try then you will understand why. Roti canai gravy + sambal I would say the best tasting near Aspira homes area. Fried chicken + nasi lemak is not bad also. Easy, convenient and very very reasonable price, keep it up!

They have nice food for breakfast and lunch. The prices are also quite reasonable, with spending less than RM10 per meal (rice, chicken, and vegetables) and water. If you take more, they will definitely charge extra.
Excellent nasi lemak. Sells out very quickly in the morning. Rest of the dishes are very good too. Offshoot of the original Dâ€™Simpang further down the road.
By objective, the food is delicious and cheap. Environment is acceptable for easy going person
Very delicious food are great price
